<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3979] Yarn backend&apos;s default file replication should match HDFS&apos;s default one</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3979</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This code in ClientBase.scala sets the replication used for files uploaded to HDFS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    val replication = sparkConf.getInt(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;spark.yarn.submit.file.replication&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, 3).toShort
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead of a hardcoded &quot;3&quot; (which is the default value for HDFS), it should be using the default value from the HDFS conf (&quot;dfs.replication&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
